RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 1 1000 Y Dirt CR: 91. Allowance Purse 50000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A SWEEPSTAKE RACE. Three Year Olds, 126 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. At time of entry, The Owner or Trainer must declare if they will run in own silks. If not declared silks will default to the NTL Silks. (No Points will be generated from this race). See Racing Office For More Info.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHISKY MY GOD (ARG) led between, met bid, best. WINDING advanced 3-4wide. fanned 5wide, up 2nd. HEAD FOR BUSINESS pressed 3wide, drifted in/steady 1/16. PROUD VETERAN stalked 3wide, bested rest. MINDSHARE stalked between, one paced. EL DIABLO ROJO saved ground, lacked rally. BOUND TO BET settled 2wide, no rally. PROJECT LEADER chased inside, retreated.

ENTRY.NAME: Proud Veteran
ENTRY.OWNER: McCurdy Ann and Pitnick Brian J

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TROUBLE N PARADISE sent for the lead, assumed a clear advantage on the backstretch, continued clear on the turn, spurted away in upper stretch and held well. CARELESS STAR chased leader two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, proved no match for rival in upper stretch, and stayed on to be a clear second. FLASHY PASS tracked pace three wide on the backstretch, continued off the rail on the turn, entered lane in the three path and quickly drifted in, had a brief battle with inside rival and kept on to be third. MO CONNELLY settled off the pace two wide on the backstretch, continued off the rail on the turn, entered lane three wide and responded well to urging to finish willingly. AFTER SUNDOWN stalked pace two wide on the backstretch, continued off the rail on the turn, entered lane along the rail and weakened while being in tight. FLAG SALUTE stayed near rail throughout and failed to threaten when asked in the lane. SECRET OF WAR away cleanly, showed brief speed chasing the clear leader, began to lose ground on the turn and tired in the lane. PLEASE NOTE, DUE TO TIMER MALFUNCTION, RACE WAS HAND TIMED

ENTRY.NAME: Flag Salute
ENTRY.OWNER: Blue Sky Training Center and Spasiano Alexander J

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 3 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RESTLESS RAMBLER sent clear, continued clear on the turn, floated out rival into the lane, dug in when rival came to his flank and repelled said rival to prove best. EPIC DRAMA tracked two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, floated out by rival into the lane, took aim in the four path and repelled by game rival. MILEYS BLUECAT stalked paced two to three wide on the backstretch, continued off the rail on the turn, swung widest into the lane and kept to task to be a clear third. LOUD FUSAICHI track pace along the rail on the backstretch, stayed along the rail through the turn and into the lane, kept on late to hold position. B D R DRAGSTER settled off the pace on the backstretch, stayed near railed throughout and made mild progress in the lane. NAUGHTY CHILD away well, settled to stalk the pace along the rail on the backstretch, continued along the inside and failed to improve in the lane. ELUSIVE VIRTUE tossed head and came away slowest, went to rail on the backstretch, continued to save ground and lacked response in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Restless Rambler
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent clear, drifted into stretch, dug in, repelled foe

ENTRY.NAME: Elusive Virtue
ENTRY.COMMENT: head turned, off slow, inside, no threat

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 4 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $2,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibi lity).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MACHO SAM vied for lead under a light urging, kept on leaders flank on the turn, dueled in the stretch and proved best late. POLLO D'ORO away best, went to rail and led along the inside heading into the turn, continued to lead entering the lane, dueled with rival in the lane and grudgingly bested late. NOT GONNA LAST shifted in and solidly bumped rival early, stalked pace three deep on the backstretch, continued three wide on the turn, entered lane in the four path, and kept on gamely. OMAHA RUTSCH settled along the inside on the backstretch, continued near the rail on the turn, launched bid two wide in the lane and kept to task to the wire. MONGOLIAN MASTER away cleanly, bumped hard by shifting in rival early, dropped to rear of the field, made progress on the turn advancing two wide, eased out to get around rival entering the lane and kept on in a good try. SMUGGLER'S COVE stalked pace in between rivals on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn and lacked needed response in the lane. WEGOTBEERONICE broke out while coming away last, stalked pace four deep on the backstretch, continued the wide journey on the turn, fanned five wide in the lane and weakened mid stretch. STORMY JOE stalked pace along the inside of three rivals, continued to hold the rail on the turn, launched a brief bid at the top of the lane, but quickly flattened mid stretch. MISSING MAURICE settled off the pace and off the rail on the backstretch, continued three wide on the turn, fanned very wide into the lane and quickly flattened out. FRIENDLY SHUFFLE broke in, dropped back and stayed on the rail throughout, and lacked any response in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Stormy Joe
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside, brief bid inside, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Omaha Rutsch
ENTRY.OWNER: Belt Bruce and De Jesus Pablo Alejandro

ENTRY.NAME: Mongolian Master
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped hard early, advanced 2wide, eased 3wide 1/8, trying

ENTRY.NAME: Not Gonna Last
ENTRY.COMMENT: shifted in/bumped early, stalked 3deep, bid 3wide, game
